Thinking of a way to wrap up the year gave me serious anxiety! I was even given the option to get paid by Instagram for making a 2022 recap & I couldn’t meet the deadline - VERY unlike me😂

The truth is… I’m really happy. I mean the happiest I’ve ever been in my life. I thought if I somehow spoke that into existence it would go away. I took major risks leading up to 2022, moving my family to a new city and becoming the sole income provider in our house. It was A LOT. But the reward is HERE.

I watch Adley play on the beach almost every week and my husband who often came home stressed out from work is suddenly lighter and happier too. 

My business hit a major milestone this year that I dreamt about for years. I learned a lot about being a leader and choosing the right team. The women making @loveyoursocialmedia possible each have their own incredible talent and ambition. I learn from them every day. 

I’m not sure where I go from here, but the view is looking pretty good so far. Thank you to all of you who lift me up and have been so encouraging so far. We are doing it!!💓🎉

Calling all OG Instagram lovers, this one is for you!🔥

A LOT of our social media clients complain about not being able to just post a photo on the platform anymore. Well BIG news, Instagram chief @mosseri said…

“I think we were overfocused on video in 2022 and pushed ranking too far, and basically showed too many videos and not enough photos. We’ve since balanced, so things like how often someone likes photos versus videos, and how often someone comments on photos versus videos, are roughly equal, which is a good sign that things are balanced.”

Here’s to @kyliejenner being happy “Instagram is becoming Instagram again!”😂 What do you think? And you guys know I’m a girl who loves her videos!!

Tag a friend who will love this change 👇

META NEWS📣 You will soon be able to buy a verification subscription. 

@zuck announced Meta will be rolling out a way for people to get verified on Facebook and Instagram with $11.99 on web and $14.99 per month on mobile. Zuckerberg described it as a “subscription service that lets you verify your account with a government ID, get a blue badge, get extra impersonation protection against accounts claiming to be you, and get direct access to customer support.”

It’s notoriously hard to get a hold of FB or IG, so having customer support could be huge! 🎉 What do you think? Will you buy it? Tell us below! #socialmedianews

I quit my “dream job” over 6 years ago.

I wanted to be a TV journalist, telling stories and I did it. I covered presidential elections, natural disasters and crimes that are now being made into documentaries. But I changed my mind. I wanted something new, something that brought me more joy and I’ve never been happier running @loveyoursocialmedia.💓

It’s ok if you no longer feel aligned to your “dream job”. We are ever evolving, and ever changing.

Honor that.

Save this as a reminder, and share with someone who needs to hear this, too. 💞 If it resonates with you, let me know below 😊

The difference 1 year can make 🎉

I wanted to share our client @spilledmilkmamma’s story (with permission from her of course). Today is her birthday and it’s also the anniversary of us starting to work together. 🥂 When we connected, she had just started sharing her story of losing her husband with 2 small kids at home and her words moved people. Suddenly, she had companies wanting to work with her. We started with small brand deals and soon she was able to quit her teaching job. She replaced that salary in months with dream partnerships and hard work. 

She’s an incredible case study on how social media can build you a life 💓 So proud to know her and work with her!

Is TikTok going to get banned in the US?🚨

Here’s what you need to know 👇

📲 Two main US gov concerns: Data sharing and what TikTok’s algorithm is feeding American users

📲 The Biden Administration warned TikTok it could be banned in the US if it doesn’t sell the app

📲 TikTok parent company ByteDance denies it has given user data to the Chinese government

📲 TikTok’s CEO is testifying March 23 for a House Committee 

We still recommend brands have a presence on TikTok because it’s a huge opportunity for brand awareness. However, it’s why you don’t put all your social media eggs in one platform! What are your thoughts? Will this change how you use TikTok?

How this dream of mine has grown💓

I remember the first person I hired full-time…I had this ever present knot of anxiety in my stomach. How could I be responsible for someone’s salary and livelihood?😬 With each new hire, the nerves drifted further and further into the background. 

My goals shifted from being solely focused on revenue, to getting these women who trusted me with their careers PTO, health insurance, 401K and paid maternity leave. I’m so proud of how far we’ve come. Sometimes I’m moving so fast, I forget to stop and soak it in. 

So thankful for this team each and every day💓

I used to be SO SCARED to request a day off in TV news. 

Would it jeopardize my chances of get promoted? Making more money? Having a better schedule? For years, traveling was so difficult and FORGET IT if you wanted a holiday off. 😩

When I started @loveyoursocialmedia I remember Aaron heading to work on Memorial Day and me opening my laptop. Aaron said, “Why are you working today?” I said, “What do you mean? It’s a Monday.” I realized then I could give myself holidays off, what a concept! 😂

Anyways, here’s to making our own schedules, traveling more and trying not to drown in parent guilt 🥂

So proud of our sweet girl!🔥 Adley is featured on the @todayshow's website as one of the top trending stories!🎉 Her story is also trending on Apple News!

Adley feeling empowered to say no to sitting on Santa's lap even though she saw kids before her do it, has resonated with so many. There were so many times growing up I felt like I just needed to be polite and hug someone I didn't want to or keep that hand on my back for way too long. I want Adley to know it will always be her choice and she has the power to use "no" as a full sentence.

She will never be forced to smile, give hugs or kisses to family or even her parents (although we love how affectionate she is). I think she can still be friendly without having to welcome physical touch if shes not up for it. 

A big thanks to @therevsanta who I've since connected with after this story went viral! He said he went home after this holiday event and wrote in his journal that talking to Adley was the most valuable thing he did that night 🥹He said he felt like it was the reason he was there that night. So special 🩷

.
.
.
